Diversity, Equity and Inclusion (DE&I). NCR believes in the power and value of diversity and strives to build a globally inclusive workplace where all people are treated fairly. The Board of Directors and its Risk Committee have direct oversight of DE&I activities. In 2020, we appointed a DE&I leader to oversee NCRís DE&I programs and goals. Our key initiatives in 2020 included, amongst others:
ïdriving workforce diversity guidance programs, which include a quarterly DE&I learning and speaker series;
ïactivating a supplier diversity program that invests in small businesses, as well as minority, women and veteran-owned business enterprises;
ïcreating the Global Inclusion Council (GIC), under the executive sponsorship of our President and Chief Executive Officer, and our Senior Vice President and Chief Human Resources Officer, with the mission to inspire action that attracts top talent, creates an inclusive work environment that values the diversity of life experiences and perspectives, and encourages innovation in pursuit of NCRís mission; and
ïsponsoring various Business Resource Groups (BRGs), which are voluntary, employee-led groups that foster a diverse, equitable, and inclusive workplace aligned with NCRís mission, values, goals, business practices and objectives, including NCRís Black Professionals Forum, Women in NCR, and United (LGBTQIA+). We look to support additional BRGs where it will help support our employees.
